sVnews
p4
VAs part of the 12th annual Sankranti Music Festival organised by the Vidwan R. K. Srikantan Trust, three CDs will be released.Apoorva Varna Rathnamala(containing 12 rare varnams of master composers rendered by Srikantan and Ramakanth);Vintage Melodies  -   Live Concert Series No.1(1979 concert recording of Swati Tirunal compositions by Srikantan and Ramakanth) andBhajana Seyave O Mansa(concert recording of late Vidwan Sandhyavandanam Srinivasa Rao).Sandhyavandanam Srinivasa Rao, a doyen of Carnatic classical music, had specialised in Muttuswami Dikshitar's kritis and his repertoire is considered a golden treasury of the great composer's works. He was also a comprehensive authority on the compositions of the Haridasas, Tyagaraja, Shyama Shastri, Kshetragna and Bhadrachala Ramadoss. Having served in various capacities at AIR Madras and Vijayawada, he popularised many programmes likeRaga DarshanaandSangeeta Shikshana.He was widely acclaimed for his stewardship as Principal of the Central College of Carnatic Music and Teacher's College of Music of the Music Academy, both at Chennai.The festival will be held between January 16 and 19, Seva Sadan Hall, Malleswaram 14th cross. Everyday the concerts are between 5 p.m. and 9 p.m.Bottom Template Starts
